{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_01Ha38q2hFLTcSZe74JmFs3v","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-20250514","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully updated the `sandbox_message.py` file to make Claude's responses more user-friendly and display todos clearly. Here are the key improvements:\n\n### 1. **Enhanced Tool Display**\n- Added meaningful icons for different tools (📝 TodoWrite, 💻 Bash, 📖 Read, etc.)\n- Tool usage is now displayed with clear formatting and line breaks\n- Tool names are bolded for better visibility\n\n### 2. **Todo List Visibility**\n- TodoWrite operations now show the actual todo items with:\n  - Status icons: ⏳ (pending), 🔄 (in_progress), ✅ (completed)\n  - Priority badges: 🔴 (high), 🟡 (medium), 🟢 (low)\n  - Clear indentation and formatting\n- TodoRead results display the current todo list in a formatted way\n\n### 3. **Improved Result Formatting**\n- Tool results are shown with ✓ for success and ❌ for errors\n- Longer content is truncated with \"...\" to maintain readability\n- Web search results and documents have dedicated formatting\n\n### 4. **Better System Messages**\n- System initialization shows model, available tools, and working directory in a structured format\n- Success/Error messages display duration, cost, and other metrics clearly\n- Durations are shown in seconds (s) or milliseconds (ms) based on length\n\n### 5. **User-Friendly Content**\n- All messages use appropriate emojis and formatting\n- Information is presented in bullet points for clarity\n- Technical details are preserved but presented in a more digestible format\n\nThe code passes all linting checks and maintains backward compatibility while significantly improving the user experience."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2031,"cache_read_input_tokens":60396,"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af5b5fd7-5d0e-4269-9952-bd44b08198b7"}
